dataCsv.Site_Description: The hull is mostly intact but the deck and port corner of the stern has collapsed. The Aloha is a double centerboard schooner and both centerboard trunks are visible. The rudder is gone but the mounting beam is extant on site along with an anchor windlass and donkey boiler. the Effie Mae, a purposely sunk dive boat rests on the starboard side near the stern of the boat. It was added as a diving attraction.
